# AI Project Rules - Java Multi-Module Template

## MANDATORY PRE-FLIGHT
- ASK FIRST: project_name, group_id
- NEVER ASSUME: version upgrades, dependency changes
- USE EXACT: Java 21, Spring Boot 3.5.4, WebFlux+Netty
- TEST: `mvn clean install` must pass after changes

## MODULE STRUCTURE
*-parent (pom) → <parent>spring-boot-starter-parent 3.5.4</parent> + <dependencyManagement>
*-api (jar) → interfaces only, depends on model
*-model (jar) → POJOs/entities, parent dependency only  
*-rest (jar) → controllers, depends on api+model

## CRITICAL RULES
- Annotations (@RequestMapping, @GetMapping) in INTERFACES, not controllers
- Controllers: @RestController only, implement interface
- Folders: create for features, NOT classes (examples = reference only)
- Dependencies: Model → API → REST (no circular)
- Reactive: Use Mono/Flux patterns

## PACKAGE STRUCTURE
com.[groupId].__PRODUCT__.__FEATURE__/[controller|service|repository]

## USAGE
**Claude Code:** "Create project using .ai-rules. Project: X, Group: Y"
**Cursor:** "@codebase Follow .ai-rules to build project X"  
**Copilot:** "Use .ai-rules to create Spring project X"

